{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 05:02:48.889399", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary of Network Health\\n- Status: Critical control-plane outage causing a complete data-plane blackout.\\n- Symptom: No host-to-host connectivity, including hosts on the same leaf and same subnet.\\n\\nKey Observations and Evidence\\n1) End-to-end reachability\\n- host_1_1 -> host_1_2 (same leaf, same /24): 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”.\\n- host_1_1 -> host_2_1 / host_2_2 (cross-leaf): 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”.\\n- host_2_1 -> host_2_2 (same leaf): 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable”.\\n- On host_1_1, ARP entries for peers (10.0.0.2, 10.0.0.9, 10.0.0.10) are FAILED, indicating ARP broadcast frames are not being forwarded by the switch.\\n\\n2) Host configurations\\n- All tested hosts (host_1_1, host_1_2, host_2_1, host_2_2) have correct IPs in 10.0.0.0/24 and link state UP. Local routes are correct (10.0.0.0/24 via eth0).\\n\\n3) Switch control-plane state (OVS)\\n- All switches are configured with an OpenFlow controller at tcp:20.0.0.100:6633 and fail_mode: secure:\\n  - leaf_1: is_connected = false; status last_error=\"Connection refused\"; state=BACKOFF.\\n  - leaf_2: is_connected = false; status last_error=\"Connection refused\"; state=BACKOFF.\\n  - spine_1: is_connected = false; status last_error=\"Connection refused\"; state=BACKOFF.\\n- No flows installed on any switch (ovs-ofctl dump-flows returns empty).\\n\\n4) Data-plane effect\\n- With fail_mode=secure and no controller connection, OVS drops all traffic (no fallback bridging). This explains failed ARP and 100% ICMP loss even between hosts on the same leaf.\\n\\nAnomalies Identified\\n- Systemic anomaly: All OVS devices are disconnected from the SDN controller and have zero flows while in secure mode.\\n- Side note on topology: leaf_1 appears dual-homed to spine_1 (spine_1:eth0<->leaf_1:eth2 and spine_1:eth2<->leaf_1:eth3). This asymmetry is not causing the current outage (since the data plane is entirely blocked), but it is noteworthy for later validation.\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Primary faulty element: The SDN controller endpoint at 20.0.0.100:6633.\\n  - “Connection refused” indicates the IP is reachable but the service is not listening on port 6633 (or is immediately rejecting connections).\\n- Secondary affected elements: All three OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) default to dropping traffic due to fail_mode=secure with no controller attachment.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- The OpenFlow controller at 20.0.0.100 is not accepting connections on port 6633 (service not running, not listening, or port misconfiguration). As a result, no flows are programmed on the switches, and with fail_mode=secure all traffic is dropped, causing a complete host-to-host connectivity failure., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='81adafbb-c03c-435e-885a-9ee0dabb9868'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
